{"lemma":"جَنْبَيْ","slug":"جَنْبَيْ","root":"ج.ن.ب","root_slug":"ج-ن-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ن-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جَنْب","root":"جنب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":32},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6415","n6416","n6417","n6418"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn aside, decline"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to refuse, turn off"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to remove"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shun, flee from"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hit sideways"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be far off"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to keep far"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shun, avoid"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause to avoid"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to miss, long for"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lead by the side"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to place a horse as leader beside another"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be a stranger, reside among strangers"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to blow from the south"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to blow towards the south"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to suffer from pleurisy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be exposed to the south wind"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to keep far, to remove to a distance","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause (one) to avoid (something or someone)","tags":["ditransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"فَأَنْذَرْتُكُمْ نَارًا تَلَظَّى / لَا يَصْلَاهَا إِلَّا الْأَشْقَى / الَّذِي كَذَّبَ وَتَوَلَّىٰ / وَسَيُجَنَّبُهَا الْأَتْقَى / الَّذِي يُؤْتِي مَالَهُ يَتَزَكَّىٰ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put aside"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lead walking by the side"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be distant from","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَنَبَ (janaba, “to turn aside, refuse”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side, flank, half of the body","examples":[{"text":"ذَات الْجَنْب","english":"pleurisy"},{"text":"ذُو الْجَنْب","english":"afflicted with pleurisy"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"boundary"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"coast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tract, region"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"principal part"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"combat, battle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reproach"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَنَبَ (janaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"in a state of major (ritual) impurity"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Root ج ن ب (j n b), a Proto-Semitic noun *ganb- (“side”)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒa.na.ba/","/d͡ʒu.ni.ba/","/d͡ʒan.na.ba/","/d͡ʒanb/","/d͡ʒa.nab/","/d͡ʒu.nub/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6415","headword_ar":"جَنْبٌ","root":"jnb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", a word of well-known meaning; (S;) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lateral half,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iq~N","text_ar":"شِقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) of a man &c.; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janabapN","text_ar":"جَنَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is beneath the arm-pit, extending to the flank;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the person: (Msb:) pl. (of the first, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junuwbN","text_ar":"جُنُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and [of the same, a pl. of pauc.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajonaAbN","text_ar":"اَجْنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(CK) and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAnibu","text_ar":"جَوَانِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, ISd, K, but not in the CK) and [app. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobN","text_ar":"جَنْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layaAy^ilu","text_ar":"لَيَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolN","text_ar":"لَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janabapN","text_ar":"جَنَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAy^iju","text_ar":"حَوَايِجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjapN","text_ar":"حَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawajapN","text_ar":"حَوَجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") or of both these] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janAy^ibu","text_ar":"جَنايِبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) which is extr. (M, TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEadotu A_ilaY","text_ar":"قَعَدْتُ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobi fulaAnK","text_ar":"جَنْبِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"flAn","text_ar":"فلان"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlY jaAnibi","text_ar":"الى جَانِبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sat by the side of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: both meaning the same. (S.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lamunotafixu AljawaAnibi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَمُنْتَفِخُ الجَوَانِبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is inflated in the side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jwAnb","text_ar":"جوانب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here one of those words which are used in the sing. sense though in the pl. form. (Lh, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTaAhu Aljanoba","text_ar":"اَعْطَاهُ الجَنْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him the side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, submissive, manageable, easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tractable, to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAru Aljanobi","text_ar":"جَارُ الجَنْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who cleaves to one, keeping by one's side."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [Differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAru Aljunubi","text_ar":"جَارُ الجُنُبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. infrà.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aAHibu","text_ar":"الصَّاحِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAljanobi","text_ar":"بِالجَنْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur iv. 40]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The travelling-companion; the companion in a journey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who is near one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by one's side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the companion in every good affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu Aljanobi","text_ar":"ذَاتُ الجَنْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) with which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljunaAbu","text_ar":"الجُنَابُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn., (K,) [and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljanobu","text_ar":"الجَنْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as will be seen in what follows,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well-known disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pleurisy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"called by the first of these three appellations in the present day;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a severe disease, being an inflammatory tumour in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleura,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"membrane within the ribs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ulcer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a purulent pustule, that comes within a man's side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a severe disease in the side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to El-Hejeree, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in either side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and they assert that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is in the left side, the patient perishes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to ISh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dubayolap","text_ar":"دُبَيْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ulcer that penetrates into the belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ulcer"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dubayolap","text_ar":"دُبَيْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~al","text_ar":"دُمَّل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that comes forth within the side, and discharges internally; the sufferer from which seldom recovers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"he who suffers from it [and dies in consequence], or, as some say, he who is afflicted by a complaint of the side (absolutely) while warring in the cause of God, is reckoned a martyr: (TA:) [soldiers in a campaign are notoriously more subject to it than persons in most other circumstances; and it is app. for this reason that] it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daA='u AlS~anaAdiydi","text_ar":"دَا=ءُ الصَّنَادِيدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the disease of the courageous chiefs]. (A, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljanobi","text_ar":"الجَنْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu Aljunobi","text_ar":"ذَاتُ الجُنْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the fem., signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having a complaint of his side by reason of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the disease above mentioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ubayolap","text_ar":"الدُّبَيْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majonuwbN","text_ar":"مَجْنُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Aln~aAsu janobN waAlA^amiyru janobu"},{"kind":"page_break","n":466},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people are a side and the prince is a side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Akh, S, TA:) as though he reckoned the latter equal to all the people. (TA. [This is cited in the S and TA as though it were an ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jnb","text_ar":"جنب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense here next following: but it seems to be rather an ex. of this word in the sense first explained in the present paragraph.]) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAHiyapN","text_ar":"نَاحِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lateral,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an outward"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjacent, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, region, quarter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a part, region, quarter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, considered with respect to its collocation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juxtaposition"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"considered as belonging to a whole; a vicinage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neighbourhood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbN","text_ar":"جَنَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobapN","text_ar":"جَنْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janabapN","text_ar":"جَنَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbapN","text_ar":"جَنَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) It is said that the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobN","text_ar":"جَنْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the part of the body mentioned in the beginning of this paragraph, and that its use in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAHyapN","text_ar":"نَاحيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is metaphorical, as is the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamiynN","text_ar":"يَمِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAlN","text_ar":"شِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAHiyapN","text_ar":"نَاحِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned in the Msb as the primary signification of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF, TA;) though its primary signification accord. to the K and ISd seems to be that first mentioned. (TA.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$awoA jaAnibayohi","text_ar":"مَشَوْا جَانِبَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbayohi","text_ar":"جَنَابَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobatayohi","text_ar":"جَنْبَتَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbatayohi","text_ar":"جَنَابَتَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They walked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went on foot, on either side of him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA. *) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~uwA yasiyruwna janaAbayohi","text_ar":"مَرُّوا يَسِيرُونَ جَنَابَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobatayohi","text_ar":"جَنْبَتَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbatayohi","text_ar":"جَنَابَتَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They went along journeying on either side of him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kun~aA Eanohumo","text_ar":"كُنَّا عَنْهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaA bayoni","text_ar":"جَنَا بَيْنِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbFA","text_ar":"جَنَابًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We were apart from them"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on two sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on one side"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazaluwA","text_ar":"نَزَلُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY janaAbaAti","text_ar":"فِى جَنَابَاتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They alighted in the sides of the valley,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the tracts beside the valley"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA yaTuwru bijanabatinaA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا يَطُورُ بِجَنَبَتِنَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one will not approach our quarter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) thus accord. to AO; with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":": IJ, however, says, people are wont to say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA fiY *araAka wajanabatika","text_ar":"اَنَا فِى ذَرَاكَ وَجَنَبَتِكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am under thy protection and in thy quarter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but that the correct expression is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobatika","text_ar":"جَنْبَتِكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent. (IB, TA.) The Arabs also said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suhayolK","text_ar":"سُهَيْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHar~u jaAnibaYo","text_ar":"الحَرُّ جَانِبَىْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The heat is on either side of Suheyl"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Canopus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during the period next before, and that next after, the auroral rising of Canopus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which rising began, in central Arabia, at the commencement of the era of the Flight, about the 4th of August, O. S.]: this is the greatest heat. (TA.) One also says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaATuwA bihi mino jaAnibayohi","text_ar":"اَحَاطُوا بِهِ مِنْ جَانِبَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They surrounded him on all his sides;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on his two sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; dividing the surrounding parts into two, but not meaning that any of these remained vacant. (Expos. of the exs. cited as testimonies by Sb, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwl","text_ar":"حول"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  Also, [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is thus used in the L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jnH","text_ar":"جنح"},{"kind":"text","text":", and by many authors,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; (L;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; (L, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great part"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (L.) Hence, [or perhaps from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobN","text_ar":"جَنْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the second of the senses assigned to it above, conveying the idea of juxtaposition, and thus of comparison,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA qaliylN janobi mawad~atika","text_ar":"هٰذَا قَلِيلٌ جَنْبِ مَوَدَّتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is little in comparison with the magnitude of thy love;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or simply,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in comparison with thy love"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA HasorataA EalaY maA far~aTotu fiY jnobi A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"يَا حَسْرَتَا عَلَى مَا فَرَّطْتُ فِى جنْبِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur xxxix. 57] means ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY jaAnibih","text_ar":"فى جَانِبِه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O my grief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regret, for my negligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remissness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of that which is the right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, of God!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Bd, TA,) i. e., (Bd,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of obedience to God!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the means of attaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearness to God!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA;) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearness to God in Paradise!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of the way of God, to which He hath called me!"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., the profession of his unity, and the confession of the prophetic office of Mohammad. (Zj, TA.) The saying of the Arabs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~aqi A@ll~`ha fiY janobihi walaA taqodaHo fiY saAqihi","text_ar":"اِتَّقِ ا@للّٰهَ فِى جَنْبِهِ وَلَا تَقْدَحْ فِى سَاقِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[may be rendered (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fear God in respect of his"},{"kind":"text","text":"(thy brother's)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, and impugn not his honour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] means, accord. to the copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taqotulohu","text_ar":"لَا تَقْتُلْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slay him not"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or, as in the L, and in the original draught of the author [of the K]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA tagotalohu","text_ar":"لا تَغْتَلْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slay him not clandestinely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on an occasion of inadvertence"},{"kind":"text","text":"], from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algiylapu","text_ar":"الغِيلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and throw him not into trouble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trial:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY jnbh","text_ar":"فى جنبه"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in detracting from his reputation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reviling him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 240.]) A poet, cited by IAar, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"xaliylaY~a kuf~aA waA@*okuraA A@ll~`ha fiY janobiY"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O my two friends, refrain, and be mindful of God in respect of my reputation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in detracting from my reputation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reviling me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to MF,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in my case."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA faEalota fiY janobi","text_ar":"مَا فَعَلْتَ فِى جَنْبِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjatiY","text_ar":"حَاجَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What didst thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what hast thou done, in the case of the thing that I want?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","Msb","CK","M","S","TA","Akh","L","Bd","Jel","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n6416","headword_ar":"جَنَبٌ","root":"jnb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janiybN","text_ar":"جَنِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawoEu Aljanabi","text_ar":"طَوْعُ الجَنَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jinaAbN","text_ar":"جِنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janabN","text_ar":"جَنَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Short;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) applied to a man. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6417","headword_ar":"جَنِبٌ","root":"jnb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janiba","text_ar":"جَنِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  It is also applied as an epithet to a wolf, because he pretends to halt, from guile, or cunning. (L, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who goes aside,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a distance, from the beaten way, for fear of guests' coming to him for entertainment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6418","headword_ar":"جُنُبٌ","root":"jnb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (El-Fárábee, S, A, Msb, K,) which is sometimes used in the sing. form as pl., and has no fem. form, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajonabiY~N","text_ar":"اَجْنَبِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (El-Fárábee, S, Msb, K,) which is said by Az in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwH","text_ar":"روح"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be seldom or never used by the Arabs, but is mentioned by him in its proper art., (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajonabu","text_ar":"اَجْنَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, S, Msb, K,) are syn., (El-Fárábee, S, Msb, K,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stranger;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janiybN","text_ar":"جَنِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or a man who is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote, in respect of relationship:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az and Msb in explanation of the third and fourth:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not a relation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as will be seen from what follows:] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAnibN","text_ar":"جَانِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as an act. part. n.] signifies one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alighting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descending and abiding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"settling, as a stranger, among a tribe:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajonaAbN","text_ar":"اَجْنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) and of the second"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jun~aAbN","text_ar":"جُنَّابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) and of the fourth"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajaAnibu","text_ar":"اَجَانِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaAru","text_ar":"الجَارُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljunubu","text_ar":"الجُنُبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[occurring in the Kur iv. 40] (T, S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAru Aljunubi","text_ar":"جَارُ الجُنُبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The person who is one's neighbour, but who belongs to another people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, A, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is not of one's family nor of one's lineage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is of another lineage than he of whom he is a neighbour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is not a relation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote, in an absolute sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the person who is not a relation to another, and who comes to him, and asks him to protect him, and abides with him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"such has the title to respect that belongs to him as neighbour of the other, and to his protection, and as relying upon his safeguard and promise. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jwr","text_ar":"جور"},{"kind":"text","text":". [Differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAru Aljanobi","text_ar":"جَارُ الجَنْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. suprà.]) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo A^ajonaAbu Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"هُمْ اَجْنَابُ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are the strangers of mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAla lijaAriy~pK halo mino mugaribapi","text_ar":"قَالَ لِجَارِيّةٍ هَلْ مِنْ مُغَرِبَةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxabaru","text_ar":"الخَبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarK qaAlato EalaY jaAnibK","text_ar":"خَبَرٍ قَالَتْ عَلَى جَانِبٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said to a girl, Is there any news from abroad? She answered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is for a stranger coming from a journey"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to give"},{"kind":"text","text":"such"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"news"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa","text_ar":"هُوَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min~iY","text_ar":"مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajonabiY~N","text_ar":"اَجْنَبِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a person not related to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  Also, ↓ the same four words, (of which only the last is mentioned in this sense in the S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That will not be led; intractable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junubN","text_ar":"جُنُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also an epithet from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljanaAbapu","text_ar":"الجَنَابَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) signifying A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"under the obligation of performing a total ablution, by reason of sexual intercourse and discharge of the semen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA: [see 4:]) and is used alike as masc. and fem. (S, Mgh, Msb) and sing. (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and dual (Msb, TA) and pl.; (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) being regarded as quasi-coordinate to the class of inf. ns.; for the inf. n., when used as an epithet, must remain, in form, sing. and masc.: (MF in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eft","text_ar":"عفت"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or one may use the dual form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junubaAni","text_ar":"جُنُبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and sometimes they used the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajonaAbN","text_ar":"اَجْنَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junubuwna","text_ar":"جُنُبُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and the fem. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junubaAtN","text_ar":"جُنُبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junubapN","text_ar":"جُنُبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) applied to a female. (TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tadoxulu AlmalaAy^ikapu biyotFA fiyhi junubN","text_ar":"لَا تَدْخُلُ المَلَايِكَةُ بِيْتًا فِيهِ جُنُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The angels will not enter a house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent, in which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who usually neglects the total ablution when under an obligation to perform it for the cause above mentioned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","Az","S","K","A","T","MF","Mgh"]}]}}